---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Goodwill letter to ask a healthcare provider to remove a paid medical collection from your credit report. Free template with instructions.";
---

<Base title="Medical Debt Goodwill Letter Template — CreditCookbook" description="{description}" posterTitle="GOODWILL LETTER" posterLabel="// 09 — goodwill removal request">
  <section class="section" data-animate>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label" data-animate>// content</span>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Goodwill letter for paid medical debt</h2>
      <p style="max-width: 64ch; margin-bottom: 32px;">A goodwill letter is a polite request asking the original creditor to remove a negative mark as a gesture of goodwill — not because they're legally required to. This works best for <strong>paid</strong> medical collections where you have a genuine hardship story and a history of on-time payments.</p>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 16px;">When goodwill letters work</h3>
<ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 32px;">
  <li>The debt is already paid</li>
  <li>You had a genuine hardship (job loss, medical emergency, family death)</li>
  <li>You've since established a positive payment history</li>
  <li>The collection was an isolated incident</li>
</ul>

<div class="mono-block" data-animate style="margin-bottom: 32px;">
[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR ADDRESS]
[YOUR CITY, STATE ZIP]

[DATE]

[HEALTHCARE PROVIDER / COLLECTION AGENCY]
[ADDRESS]

RE: Goodwill Request for Account Removal
Account: [ACCOUNT NUMBER]

Dear [Provider/Billing Manager],

I am writing to respectfully request that you remove
the above-referenced collection account from my credit
report as a gesture of goodwill.

I incurred this medical debt during [BRIEF HARDSHIP
DESCRIPTION: e.g., a period of unemployment / an
unexpected medical emergency / a family crisis].

The account has been paid in full as of [DATE], and
I have since maintained a positive payment history with
[PROVIDER/OTHER CREDITORS] for [TIME PERIOD].

I understand that this collection was accurately
reported, and I take full responsibility for the debt.
I am not disputing the account — I am asking for your
understanding and goodwill in removing this negative
mark so that I can [PURPOSE: e.g., qualify for a
mortgage / refinance my home / secure better loan
terms for my family].

I would be deeply grateful for your consideration.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR PHONE]
[YOUR EMAIL]
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Goodwill letter tips</h4>
  <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
    <li>Send to the original provider, not the collection agency</li>
    <li>Be genuine — explain the hardship without making excuses</li>
    <li>Keep it to one page — decision-makers skim</li>
    <li>Follow up in 30 days if no response</li>
    <li>Goodwill is discretionary — they don't have to do it</li>
    <li>Try a different contact (billing manager, patient advocate) if denied</li>
  </ul>
</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
